metadata.description:
A theme-song for the independent artist.

My mission with this song was to speak to those that question and challenge their existence in every sense of their being. There may be those that know this already, but just as a reminder, to reach success, whatever that word means, you must rid yourself of doubt and fear. Sometimes companionship and bet on yourself. All for the pursuit of happiness.

When we rid ourselves of limitations and take leaps of faith, those roads traveled are uniquely our own. It may be lonely and get dark at times, but one thing is for sure, finding that love, existing in it, whether external or self-love.

It's fuel, passion, and enough to help you reach fulfillment. 

In support of the independent artists on here, I know how challenging all of this truly is. The collector that wins the golden egg - will receive 10% of the primary sale. I encourage you to pay it forward and support more artists in this space by minting their MusicNFTs.

Thank You.

lyrics.text:
Verse:
Said, there’s got to be more to life than this
Questioned the existence
Then jumped off the precipice Goodbyes and tearful eyes
Why did I have to let most things go

Pre-Chorus: 
Well I know
That most of these things are 
Out of our control
I'm Searching for home

Chorus:
I’ve been run, run, running away 
Going against the grain
I’ll go home, cause I’m homesick 
(Let’s go home)

Verse:
Said there’s got to be more to life than this 
Searching for reverence
Instead got deliverance 
The sun shines on my dark sides
Who knew that she could be a lifeline

Pre-Chorus: 
Well I know
That most of these things are 
Out of our control 
I’m searching for home

Chorus:
I’ve been run, run running away 
Going against the grain (just go home) I’ll go home, cause I’m homesick
(let’s go home, let’s go home)
